race.comment: Cranbourne on a Saturday for the second time in a month. Rail is true and the track should play fair. EXTREME VIRTUE (1) brings the right form to the first. Two good efforts this time around and things hardly look tougher this time. They could be tougher if we see the very best of DIVINE THOUGHTS (9). Yet to see it in a couple for the new yard but she has gone back and had a kill at the trials and she has run sharp time winning by a space over the Cranbourne mile in the past. I ONLY WISH (6) just found one better last time but peaked there and showed last campaign that when she hits her form she can hold it. MISS PLAYLOUNGE (5) was well held there but she was a winner prior and gets a big jockey switch today. SIRIUS STATEMENT (3) comes through a couple of races that should hold up and produce winners.
